FuncDef:
The web-auth-server reply-message command enables a device to transparently transmit response messages from the RADIUS server to the web authentication server.
The undo web-auth-server reply-message command disables a device from transparently transmitting response messages from the RADIUS server to the web authentication server.
By default, the response messages are transparently transmitted.
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
To enable a device to transparently transmit response messages from the RADIUS server to the web authentication server, run the web-auth-server reply-message command.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
